{
  "work_slug": "the-maltese-falcon-by-dashiell-hammett",
  "work_title": "Maltese Falcon, Original Serialized Version",
  "work_author": "Dashiell Hammett",
  "audio_file": "audio-07",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/maltesefalcon_2511_librivox/maltesefalcon_07_hammett.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter 7 - G in the Air",
  "reader_name": "Mark Nelson",
  "page_num": 2,
  "page_total": 7,
  "page_start_sec": 259.936,
  "page_end_sec": 503.86,
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.735,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 259.936,
      "end": 261.56,
      "text": "Spade hadn't been told very definitely",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 261.56,
      "end": 263.16,
      "text": "what to do when he found Flitcraft."
    },
    {
      "start": 264.2,
      "end": 266.32,
      "text": "They talked in Spade's room at the Davenport.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 266.85,
      "end": 268.96,
      "text": "Flitcraft had no feeling of guilt."
    },
    {
      "start": 269.52,
      "end": 272.32,
      "text": "He had left his first family well provided for,"
    },
    {
      "start": 272.57,
      "end": 274.73,
      "text": "and what he had done seemed to him perfectly"
    },
    {
      "start": 274.84,
      "end": 275.22,
      "text": "reasonable."
    },
    {
      "start": 276.22,
      "end": 278.36,
      "text": "The only thing that bothered him was a",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 278.36,
      "end": 280.15,
      "text": "doubt that he could make its reasonableness"
    },
    {
      "start": 280.46,
      "end": 281.24,
      "text": "clear to Spade."
    },
    {
      "start": 282.3,
      "end": 284.18,
      "text": "He had never told anybody about it before,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 284.51,
      "end": 286.66,
      "text": "and thus had not had to attempt to"
    },
    {
      "start": 286.66,
      "end": 288.18,
      "text": "make its reasonableness explicit."
    },
    {
      "start": 289.36,
      "end": 290.08,
      "text": "He tried now.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 291.82,
      "end": 294.83,
      "text": "\"'I got it all right,' Spade told Bridget O'Shaughnessy.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 295.1,
      "end": 296.04,
      "text": "But Mrs."
    },
    {
      "start": 296.22,
      "end": 297.22,
      "text": "Flitcraft never did."
    },
    {
      "start": 297.92,
      "end": 298.84,
      "text": "She thought it was silly."
    },
    {
      "start": 299.712,
      "end": 300.28,
      "text": "Maybe it was.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 300.64,
      "end": 301.32,
      "text": "Anyway,"
    },
    {
      "start": 301.58,
      "end": 302.8,
      "text": "it came out all right."
    },
    {
      "start": 303.7,
      "end": 304.94,
      "text": "She didn't want any scandal,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 305.14,
      "end": 307.06,
      "text": "and after the trick he had played on her,"
    },
    {
      "start": 307.24,
      "end": 308.54,
      "text": "the way she looked at it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 308.56,
      "end": 309.6,
      "text": "she didn't want him."
    },
    {
      "start": 310.78,
      "end": 312.42,
      "text": "So she divorced him on the quiet,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 312.58,
      "end": 314.5,
      "text": "and everything was swell all around."
    },
    {
      "start": 316.448,
      "end": 317.52,
      "text": "Here's what had happened to him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 318.62,
      "end": 319.3,
      "text": "Going to lunch,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 319.36,
      "end": 320.66,
      "text": "he had passed an office building,"
    },
    {
      "start": 320.98,
      "end": 323.54,
      "text": "or the skeleton of one that was being put up."
    },
    {
      "start": 324.18,
      "end": 326.36,
      "text": "A beam or something fell eight or ten"
    },
    {
      "start": 326.36,
      "end": 328.58,
      "text": "stories to the sidewalk alongside him."
    },
    {
      "start": 329.62,
      "end": 331.78,
      "text": "It brushed close to him but didn't touch him,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 332.28,
      "end": 333.5,
      "text": "though a piece of the sidewalk,"
    },
    {
      "start": 333.78,
      "end": 335.04,
      "text": "a piece of brick or cement,"
    },
    {
      "start": 335.2,
      "end": 337.58,
      "text": "was chipped off and flew up and struck him on the cheek."
    },
    {
      "start": 338.84,
      "end": 340.24,
      "text": "It only took a piece of skin off,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 340.36,
      "end": 342.44,
      "text": "but he still had the scar when I saw him."
    },
    {
      "start": 343.48,
      "end": 344.72,
      "text": "He rubbed it with his finger,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 344.88,
      "end": 345.28,
      "text": "thoughtfully,"
    },
    {
      "start": 345.92,
      "end": 347.0,
      "text": "almost affectionately,"
    },
    {
      "start": 347.04,
      "end": 348.4,
      "text": "while he told me about it."
    },
    {
      "start": 349.14,
      "end": 350.2,
      "text": "He was frightened,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 350.32,
      "end": 350.64,
      "text": "of course,"
    },
    {
      "start": 350.72,
      "end": 351.06,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 351.18,
      "end": 353.14,
      "text": "but he was more shocked than frightened."
    },
    {
      "start": 354.26,
      "end": 356.18,
      "text": "It was as if somebody had taken the lid",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 356.18,
      "end": 358.2,
      "text": "off life and let him look at the works."
    },
    {
      "start": 359.77,
      "end": 361.54,
      "text": "He had been a good citizen,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 361.76,
      "end": 362.66,
      "text": "a good husband,"
    },
    {
      "start": 362.76,
      "end": 363.78,
      "text": "and a good father,"
    },
    {
      "start": 363.96,
      "end": 366.12,
      "text": "not by any outer compulsion,"
    },
    {
      "start": 366.66,
      "end": 367.6,
      "text": "but simply because"
    },
    {
      "start": 368.14,
      "end": 369.84,
      "text": "he was the sort of man who was most"
    },
    {
      "start": 369.84,
      "end": 371.8,
      "text": "comfortable in step with his surroundings."
    },
    {
      "start": 373.18,
      "end": 374.32,
      "text": "He had been raised that way.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 374.64,
      "end": 376.62,
      "text": "The people he knew were like that."
    },
    {
      "start": 376.96,
      "end": 378.88,
      "text": "The life he knew was a clean,"
    },
    {
      "start": 379.16,
      "end": 379.76,
      "text": "orderly,"
    },
    {
      "start": 379.76,
      "end": 380.08,
      "text": "sane,"
    },
    {
      "start": 380.22,
      "end": 381.14,
      "text": "responsible affair."
    },
    {
      "start": 382.62,
      "end": 385.34,
      "text": "Now a falling beam had shown him that life",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 385.34,
      "end": 387.28,
      "text": "was fundamentally none of these things."
    },
    {
      "start": 388.06,
      "end": 388.46,
      "text": "He,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 388.72,
      "end": 389.58,
      "text": "the good citizen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 390.18,
      "end": 392.76,
      "text": "could be wiped out between real estate office and restaurant"
    },
    {
      "start": 392.98,
      "end": 394.64,
      "text": "by the accident of a falling beam."
    },
    {
      "start": 396.04,
      "end": 398.26,
      "text": "He knew then that men died at haphazard,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 398.38,
      "end": 399.16,
      "text": "like that,"
    },
    {
      "start": 399.72,
      "end": 402.02,
      "text": "and lived only while blind chance spared them."
    },
    {
      "start": 403.54,
      "end": 405.64,
      "text": "It wasn't the injustice of it that disturbed him.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 405.76,
      "end": 408.24,
      "text": "he accepted that after the first shock."
    },
    {
      "start": 409.3,
      "end": 411.66,
      "text": "What disturbed him was the discovery that,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 411.92,
      "end": 413.36,
      "text": "insensibly ordering his affairs,"
    },
    {
      "start": 413.64,
      "end": 416.88,
      "text": "he had got out of step and not into step with life."
    },
    {
      "start": 417.8,
      "end": 420.5,
      "text": "He said he knew before he had gone twenty feet",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 420.5,
      "end": 422.88,
      "text": "from the fallen beam that he would never again"
    },
    {
      "start": 422.94,
      "end": 426.5,
      "text": "know peace until he had adjusted himself to this new glimpse of life."
    },
    {
      "start": 427.5,
      "end": 428.54,
      "text": "By the time he had finished",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 428.54,
      "end": 431.04,
      "text": "his luncheon he had found his means of adjustment."
    },
    {
      "start": 432.384,
      "end": 434.7,
      "text": "Life could be ended for him at random by a falling",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 434.92,
      "end": 435.06,
      "text": "being."
    },
    {
      "start": 436.14,
      "end": 439.14,
      "text": "He would change his life at random simply by going off.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 439.968,
      "end": 441.12,
      "text": "He loved his family,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 441.22,
      "end": 441.54,
      "text": "he said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 441.64,
      "end": 443.6,
      "text": "as much as he supposed was usual,"
    },
    {
      "start": 444.42,
      "end": 446.44,
      "text": "but he knew he was leaving them provided for,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 447.04,
      "end": 449.06,
      "text": "and his love for them wasn't of the sort"
    },
    {
      "start": 449.06,
      "end": 450.94,
      "text": "that would make absence from them painful."
    },
    {
      "start": 451.79,
      "end": 453.78,
      "text": "He went to Seattle that afternoon,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 454.12,
      "end": 455.08,
      "text": "Spade said,"
    },
    {
      "start": 455.84,
      "end": 457.8,
      "text": "and from there by boat to San Francisco.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 459.1,
      "end": 461.0,
      "text": "For two or three years he roamed around the",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 461.0,
      "end": 463.02,
      "text": "country and then returned to the Northwest,"
    },
    {
      "start": 463.44,
      "end": 464.82,
      "text": "settling in Spokane."
    },
    {
      "start": 466.016,
      "end": 467.02,
      "text": "Presently he married.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 467.7,
      "end": 470.02,
      "text": "His second wife didn't look like his first,"
    },
    {
      "start": 470.34,
      "end": 471.68,
      "text": "and you could find more points of"
    },
    {
      "start": 471.68,
      "end": 473.48,
      "text": "difference than of likeness between them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 474.22,
      "end": 477.2,
      "text": "but both were the sort of women who play fair golf and bridge,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 477.92,
      "end": 479.32,
      "text": "take pains with their guest rooms,"
    },
    {
      "start": 479.72,
      "end": 481.06,
      "text": "and welcome new salad recipes."
    },
    {
      "start": 482.3,
      "end": 484.7,
      "text": "He felt that what he had done was reasonable.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 485.6,
      "end": 486.76,
      "text": "He regretted none of it.",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 487.38,
      "end": 490.5,
      "text": "I don't think that he was conscious of having stepped back naturally"
    },
    {
      "start": 490.66,
      "end": 492.2,
      "text": "into the groove he had left in Tacoma,"
    },
    {
      "start": 492.52,
      "end": 494.88,
      "text": "but that's the part of it that I like best."
    },
    {
      "start": 496.04,
      "end": 498.34,
      "text": "He had adjusted himself to the falling beam,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 498.82,
      "end": 500.86,
      "text": "and then no more beams had fallen,"
    },
    {
      "start": 500.98,
      "end": 503.86,
      "text": "and he had adjusted himself to their not falling."
    }
  ]
}